*tl;dr:* I built an upgrade skill for OpenCode that handles the entire update workflow—from refreshing Homebrew to verifying the new version—in one command.<p>Usage;
Just ask <em>Claude</em> in OpenCode:<p>&quot;Upgrade OpenCode&quot;
&quot;Update OpenCode to the latest version&quot;
&quot;Check for OpenCode updates&quot;<p><a href="https://ekadetov.github.io/2026/02/16/opencode-upgrade-skill.html" rel="nofollow">https://ekadetov.github.io/2026/02/16/opencode-upgrade-skill...</a>

